\f0\fs24 \cf0 An avatar core is a 3D bit diagram representing a Fabric name.\ A Fabric name is a 64-bit number represented as a vector\ of octets in network (big-endian) order.\ A 64-bit number can be represented as a 4x4x4 cube of bits.\ We can render this as a grid of voxels where the presence of a voxel\ represents a one, and the absence of a voxel represents a zero.\ We can render a Fabric name as a cube made of four layers, where each layer\ is a square of four rows, and each row is a sequence of four bits.\ \ We adopt the convention of rendering a fabric name as a cube by starting with\ the most-significant byte in the top left corner of the top layer of the cube. The first\ byte ( 8 bits) occupies the first two rows of that layer, followed by the second byte in the\ second two rows. Moving to the third byte, it occupies the top to rows of the\ second layer, and so on to the end of the name. Each time a one is encountered,\ we place a cube in the corresponding position in the core avatar's grid.}
